WEBVTT

00:06.465 --> 00:09.301
[♪ Naomi Banks:
"Waiting for You"]

00:14.765 --> 00:17.727
[laughs] Where's your boo?

00:17.810 --> 00:20.187
He is getting me more drinks.

00:20.271 --> 00:21.772
Uh, it seems like you have
already had a couple.

00:21.856 --> 00:22.982
Are you okay?

00:23.065 --> 00:24.942
- I'm great.
- [sighs]

00:25.025 --> 00:26.402
Here you go, angel.

00:26.485 --> 00:27.611
- Ooh.
- Mmm.

00:27.695 --> 00:29.530
- Thanks, spunky.
- Mmm.

00:29.613 --> 00:33.117
♪ And, baby, when you're gone...

00:33.200 --> 00:35.244
Oh, shoot. Give me a sec.

00:35.327 --> 00:37.580
The egg's finally here.

00:37.663 --> 00:39.790
I need to round up the other
sperm so we can take a picture.

00:39.874 --> 00:41.542
Okay, but make sure
you come back.

00:41.625 --> 00:43.502
- I'll come back.
- Okay.

00:43.586 --> 00:44.712
♪ For you...

00:44.795 --> 00:46.297
Wow. It seems like

00:46.380 --> 00:48.591
you're aggressively fine
with this breakup.

00:48.674 --> 00:50.092
I don't even know what breakup
you're talking about.

00:50.176 --> 00:51.761
Mm-hmm.

00:51.844 --> 00:53.345
♪ For you...

00:53.429 --> 00:56.223
I told you, he's not coming.

00:56.307 --> 00:58.017
I know.

00:58.100 --> 01:01.187
[chuckles] You know you can
talk to me about it, right?

01:01.270 --> 01:04.106
For the record, I thought
you guys were great together.

01:04.190 --> 01:06.400
Look, just because I was
friends with him first

01:06.484 --> 01:09.320
doesn't mean that I don't
want to be there for you, okay?

01:09.403 --> 01:10.738
Okay.

01:10.821 --> 01:13.115
I just don't want
to put you in that position.

01:13.199 --> 01:14.825
Besides, I'm not
thinking about him

01:14.909 --> 01:16.243
or-or what he's doing tonight

01:16.327 --> 01:17.953
or who he's with
or how he's feeling.

01:18.037 --> 01:19.163
How is he feeling, by the way?

01:19.246 --> 01:20.831
He's a mess. Just like you.

01:20.915 --> 01:23.167
Except you actually get
all dressed up

01:23.250 --> 01:24.960
and make out with guys
you just met,

01:25.044 --> 01:27.296
and he's been sitting
in the same gray sweatpants

01:27.379 --> 01:28.714
for the past two weeks.

01:28.798 --> 01:30.716
Damn, he looked good in those.

01:30.800 --> 01:33.302
Oh, no. I miss him.

01:33.385 --> 01:35.137
You know, he's the first person

01:35.221 --> 01:37.014
I've ever truly
been in love with.

01:37.097 --> 01:38.307
But it's not enough.

01:38.390 --> 01:39.850
No, I can't build
my life with someone

01:39.934 --> 01:41.685
that is so glass half-empty.

01:41.769 --> 01:44.605
Ooh, I hear that.
Andres isn't perfect.

01:44.688 --> 01:45.606
[girl] Go, Andres!

01:45.689 --> 01:48.484
- Come on, Andres!
- [laughter]

01:48.567 --> 01:49.944
- [Andres] Oh, oh, hey!
- [Annie] But...

01:50.027 --> 01:52.905
[laughs] ...he makes me laugh.

01:54.281 --> 01:55.366
[chuckles]

01:55.449 --> 01:57.368
♪ I'm not myself ♪

01:57.451 --> 02:01.580
♪ When I'm not with you,
baby, standing...

02:01.664 --> 02:03.207
Oh, shit. [chuckles]

02:03.290 --> 02:04.500
What?

02:04.583 --> 02:06.001
Speak of the devil.

02:06.085 --> 02:07.795
[Annie laughs]

02:07.878 --> 02:11.215
Hey! The gang's
all back together.

02:11.298 --> 02:12.842
♪ Don't forget me, baby...

02:12.925 --> 02:16.428
What are you doing here?
These are my friends.

02:16.512 --> 02:20.307
Yeah, well, they're
my friends, too, now, so...

02:20.391 --> 02:22.768
- So?
- So...

02:22.852 --> 02:24.895
now that we've broken up,

02:24.979 --> 02:27.106
we're gonna have to find
a way to share them. Mwah.

02:27.189 --> 02:28.440
- What, like, custody?
- Whoa, uh,

02:28.524 --> 02:30.109
as a child of divorce,
I find this triggering.

02:30.192 --> 02:31.485
You know what? I'm sorry, Dre.

02:31.569 --> 02:32.570
You see what you're doing
to my boy here?

02:32.653 --> 02:34.572
- He's in shambles.
- Me?

02:34.655 --> 02:35.698
You're the one
who just showed up

02:35.781 --> 02:36.824
after saying you weren't coming.

02:36.907 --> 02:38.701
Who told you that?

02:38.784 --> 02:40.494
- My good friend Annie.
- Ooh.

02:40.578 --> 02:41.745
Well, I didn't know
me saying I wasn't coming

02:41.829 --> 02:43.622
meant that you were
automatically invited.

02:43.706 --> 02:45.124
Of course that's what it means.

02:45.207 --> 02:47.042
And since when
do you go to parties?

02:47.126 --> 02:48.669
You hate people.

02:48.752 --> 02:50.004
Yeah, 'cause people
are the worst.

02:50.087 --> 02:53.132
I just walked past
two asshats dressed as sperm.

02:55.551 --> 02:58.470
There he is. Hmm? Hmm?

02:58.554 --> 03:01.891
Mr. Looks Down on Everybody to
Shield Himself from Connection.

03:01.974 --> 03:03.058
Wow, there she is.

03:03.142 --> 03:04.560
Reads Half an Article on Goop

03:04.643 --> 03:06.061
and All of a Sudden
You're a Therapist?

03:06.145 --> 03:08.147
First of all, I heard it
on the Goop podcast,

03:08.230 --> 03:09.773
and second, it's 100% true.

03:09.857 --> 03:11.567
There are two ways
of living your life,

03:11.650 --> 03:14.778
one as if nothing's a miracle,
the other as if everything is.

03:14.862 --> 03:17.740
I want to live my life
like it's a miracle.

03:17.823 --> 03:19.408
[laughs]

03:19.491 --> 03:20.910
What are you, Mary Poppins?

03:20.993 --> 03:23.370
That has to be the stupidest
thing I've ever heard.

03:23.454 --> 03:25.122
Well, Einstein said it.

03:25.205 --> 03:27.708
Who's stupid now? Huh?

03:27.791 --> 03:29.501
♪ Don't wake me up...

03:29.585 --> 03:30.794
Know what?

03:32.296 --> 03:33.505
This...

03:33.547 --> 03:34.924
♪ Whatever it takes...

03:35.007 --> 03:37.134
...this was a mistake.

03:37.217 --> 03:39.011
Good. Leave.

03:39.094 --> 03:40.596
Adiós.

03:40.679 --> 03:43.015
[Andres] Text me
when you get home, dawg.

03:43.098 --> 03:45.517
♪ We elevate ♪

03:45.601 --> 03:47.311
♪ Whatever it takes ♪

03:48.354 --> 03:51.190
♪ Whatever it takes...

03:51.273 --> 03:53.108
I'm so sorry
we ruined your party.

03:53.192 --> 03:55.945
No. Girl, don't even. [exhales]

03:56.028 --> 03:57.655
In a few hours, Andres is
gonna think it's a good idea

03:57.738 --> 03:59.365
to shave his beard
into a mustache.

03:59.448 --> 04:00.991
That is gonna ruin the party.

04:01.075 --> 04:02.284
Until then...

04:03.494 --> 04:05.537
[exhales] ...drink this.

04:05.621 --> 04:07.623
- Salud.
- Salud.

04:07.665 --> 04:08.791
♪ We're in free fall ♪

04:08.874 --> 04:10.709
[exhales] Another one.

04:10.793 --> 04:14.546
♪ Oh, we are, we are,
oh, we are, we are ♪

04:14.630 --> 04:17.341
♪ Light it up, light it up ♪

04:17.424 --> 04:19.176
♪ Ooh ♪

04:19.259 --> 04:22.429
♪ Oh, we are, we are,
oh, we are, we are ♪

04:22.513 --> 04:26.308
♪ Light it up,
we're in free fall ♪

04:26.392 --> 04:28.769
♪ We're in free fall,
la, la, la, la ♪

04:29.853 --> 04:32.815
♪ We're in free fall,
la, la, la, la ♪

04:33.857 --> 04:37.820
♪ We're in free fall,
la, la, la, la ♪

04:37.903 --> 04:41.532
♪ See a million
flashing lights ♪♪

04:46.245 --> 04:48.706
Damn.

04:48.789 --> 04:50.416
Uh-oh.

04:54.920 --> 04:56.964
- [sniffles]
- [laughs]

04:57.047 --> 04:58.716
Time to get up, angel.

05:04.263 --> 05:06.223
[grunts] Nice mustache.

05:06.306 --> 05:10.144
Uh, oh, I lost a bet with Annie,
so I got to clean the apartment

05:10.227 --> 05:11.562
and get her some Mickey D's.

05:11.645 --> 05:12.771
You want something?

05:12.855 --> 05:13.856
Mm-mm.

05:13.939 --> 05:16.817
Thank you for letting me crash.

05:16.900 --> 05:18.068
Anytime.

05:18.152 --> 05:19.820
[grunts softly]

05:19.903 --> 05:21.321
You okay?

05:22.406 --> 05:24.450
Honestly?

05:24.533 --> 05:26.577
No.

05:26.660 --> 05:28.579
But I will be.

05:28.662 --> 05:31.749
[♪ Joe Wilson:
"When a Man Cries"]

05:31.832 --> 05:34.126
- [both yawn]
- Good luck.

05:38.422 --> 05:41.759
♪ I remember, baby ♪

05:41.842 --> 05:47.222
♪ When we first met ♪

05:47.306 --> 05:50.893
♪ The way you loved me ♪

05:50.976 --> 05:55.981
♪ Oh, how can I forget? ♪

05:57.483 --> 06:00.444
♪ You treated me right ♪

06:00.527 --> 06:02.571
♪ Oh ♪

06:02.654 --> 06:06.158
♪ But I treated you wrong ♪

06:07.409 --> 06:11.747
♪ Your friends would have
to help you ♪

06:11.830 --> 06:16.126
♪ When I left you crying
at home ♪♪

06:18.962 --> 06:20.839
[church bell ringing]

06:29.181 --> 06:31.934
♪ ♪

06:46.949 --> 06:49.034
[sighs]

06:50.369 --> 06:53.622
Bless me, Father,
for I have sinned.

06:55.707 --> 06:58.043
It's been almost a year
since my last confession.

06:59.378 --> 07:00.921
Oh, forgive me
for wearing this costume

07:01.004 --> 07:02.673
in the house of the Lord.

07:02.756 --> 07:04.091
Perdóname, diosito.

07:05.092 --> 07:06.343
I'm gonna cut to the chase.

07:06.426 --> 07:08.428
Padre, I'm alone, again.

07:08.512 --> 07:11.890
I came here almost a year ago
wanting to find someone.

07:11.974 --> 07:13.392
I thought I found that person.

07:13.475 --> 07:15.060
It turns out I was wrong.

07:15.144 --> 07:19.940
So here I sit, a year
of my life, down the drain.

07:20.023 --> 07:21.483
I blame my parents.

07:21.567 --> 07:23.402
They have a perfect marriage.

07:23.485 --> 07:25.237
If they hadn't set
such an immaculate example,

07:25.320 --> 07:28.574
I wouldn't hold every
relationship I have up to it.

07:28.657 --> 07:30.659
I'm so tired.

07:32.327 --> 07:35.038
Should I just apply to be a nun?

07:35.122 --> 07:36.582
I mean, you hang out
with ladies all day

07:36.665 --> 07:39.668
and make cheese and sing songs.

07:39.751 --> 07:42.546
That could be a good life.

07:42.629 --> 07:45.382
Question:
do nuns get health care?

07:45.465 --> 07:48.051
Okay, um... [clears throat]

07:48.135 --> 07:50.721
to boil it down
to one question...

07:52.723 --> 07:54.725
What do I do now?

08:00.814 --> 08:03.650
I'm sorry about the nun thing.

08:03.734 --> 08:06.403
I was being earnest,
I wasn't making fun.

08:08.405 --> 08:11.825
Padre, it was a bad joke.
Get over it.

08:14.953 --> 08:16.788
Padre?

08:23.128 --> 08:25.464
Of course.

08:26.798 --> 08:28.550
Can I help you?

08:28.634 --> 08:31.220
Is there not someone
always in there?

08:31.303 --> 08:33.388
No, it's from 5:00 to 7:00.

08:33.472 --> 08:35.015
You could put that on a sign.

08:36.642 --> 08:38.518
[sighs]

08:38.602 --> 08:40.270
Just kidding. [chuckles]

08:40.354 --> 08:42.189
Sorry about the...

08:43.899 --> 08:45.525
Uh...

08:45.609 --> 08:47.152
Peace be with you, Father.

08:53.825 --> 08:55.827
♪ ♪

09:04.169 --> 09:06.171
[snoring]

09:09.383 --> 09:11.385
[phone ringing, vibrating]

09:18.267 --> 09:20.269
[sighs]

09:31.613 --> 09:33.615
♪ ♪

10:02.477 --> 10:04.479
♪ ♪

10:15.699 --> 10:18.452
Hey. Where's mine?

10:18.535 --> 10:19.911
- That's rude.
- [chuckles]

10:19.995 --> 10:21.830
Babe, it's 9:00 a.m.

10:21.913 --> 10:24.166
and you've already had
three cups of coffee.

10:24.249 --> 10:25.834
- Yes.
- [scoffs]

10:25.917 --> 10:29.046
Living in L.A. has turned you
into a coffee fiend.

10:29.129 --> 10:31.673
My heart actually did stop
at one point this morning,

10:31.757 --> 10:32.924
so I just drank more coffee.

10:33.008 --> 10:34.718
But I have a very
busy day ahead of me.

10:34.801 --> 10:36.136
I mean,
Chuey just sent me an email.

10:36.219 --> 10:38.263
The Día de los Muertos event
is completely sold out.

10:38.347 --> 10:41.391
Yeah, it is!
'Cause my boo is da bomb.

10:41.475 --> 10:43.769
Boo? Da bomb?

10:43.852 --> 10:46.730
Hmm. Sometimes I remember
that you're older than me.

10:46.813 --> 10:48.565
[imitates cat yowling]

10:48.648 --> 10:51.360
Sorry, babe, I'm just, I'm
making my bisabuelo's al pastor,

10:51.443 --> 10:53.904
and if I fuck it up,
he will literally haunt me

10:53.987 --> 10:55.489
because that is what
this day is all about.

10:55.572 --> 10:57.574
- [phone vibrates, chimes]
- Aw.

10:57.657 --> 10:59.743
My dad.

10:59.826 --> 11:01.536
"Good luck today, mijo.

11:01.620 --> 11:03.497
I know you'll knock it out
of the cemetery.

11:03.580 --> 11:04.790
Love you."

11:04.873 --> 11:06.583
- Aw.
- Sweet.

11:08.418 --> 11:10.879
- You okay, babe?
- Yeah.

11:10.962 --> 11:12.381
You know, I'm just missing
my family a lot today,

11:12.464 --> 11:14.132
but it's okay.

11:14.216 --> 11:15.759
I mean, we'll see them in two
weeks for Thanksgiving, so...

11:15.842 --> 11:16.885
Oh, you know what we should do?

11:16.968 --> 11:18.428
We should get
our tickets, actually.

11:18.512 --> 11:19.721
So...

11:19.805 --> 11:22.391
Uh, I was actually gonna
talk to you about that.

11:22.474 --> 11:27.104
My parents asked if they could
come visit us for Thanksgiving.

11:27.187 --> 11:28.605
Oh.

11:28.688 --> 11:30.565
I-I told them I'd have
to talk to you first,

11:30.649 --> 11:33.693
but I really want you
to finally meet them.

11:33.777 --> 11:36.029
Yeah. Yeah, no.

11:36.113 --> 11:38.240
I-I want to do that.

11:38.323 --> 11:40.075
I want to do that.
That sounds great.

11:40.158 --> 11:42.411
- Really?
- Yeah, I mean,

11:42.494 --> 11:44.037
we spent the last few holidays
with my family.

11:44.121 --> 11:46.873
It's only fair
that we spend some with yours.

11:46.957 --> 11:48.041
Ah. [grunts]

11:48.125 --> 11:49.292
You're the best.

11:49.376 --> 11:51.169
- Oh, I know.
- [exhales]

11:52.212 --> 11:53.505
In fact...

11:53.588 --> 11:55.590
you deserve this.

11:55.674 --> 11:56.883
Ah, thank you.

11:56.967 --> 11:58.510
And you deserve this.

12:00.554 --> 12:02.722
Suddenly I feel less stressed.

12:02.806 --> 12:05.517
Good. You enjoy your coffee.

12:05.600 --> 12:07.644
- Okay.
- Don't want it to get cold.

12:07.727 --> 12:09.229
Mm.

12:09.312 --> 12:10.480
[whispers] Don't move.

12:10.564 --> 12:11.648
[laughs]

12:13.608 --> 12:15.694
Wow. Okay.

12:19.239 --> 12:20.907
Mmm.

12:20.991 --> 12:24.411
Got to say, L.A.
is really growing on me.

12:24.494 --> 12:26.288
[moans]

12:26.371 --> 12:29.583
- [♪ Soraya: "Que Bonito"]
- ♪ Oye, la vida tiene
mil colores ♪

12:29.666 --> 12:32.127
♪ No solo tiene sin sabores ♪

12:32.210 --> 12:37.549
♪ Hay días que amanecen tristes
pero siempre habran mejores ♪

12:37.632 --> 12:39.426
♪ No hay mal que el tiempo
no devore ♪

12:39.509 --> 12:42.387
♪ Aunque lo bueno se demore ♪

12:42.471 --> 12:46.558
♪ Seguro llegara ese día
porque asi es la vida ♪

12:46.641 --> 12:49.978
♪ Hoy ya decidi ♪

12:50.061 --> 12:51.480
♪ Que llorar no quiero ♪

12:51.563 --> 12:54.983
♪ Voy a sonreir ♪

12:55.066 --> 12:58.028
♪ Por lo que yo tengo ♪

12:58.111 --> 12:59.863
♪ Oh ♪

12:59.946 --> 13:01.072
♪ Por lo que yo tengo ♪♪

13:01.156 --> 13:04.326
There.
Take a look.

13:05.535 --> 13:07.120
- Let's see.
- [laughs]

13:07.204 --> 13:08.455
Wow, that's so cool.

13:08.538 --> 13:09.915
I love it.
Can you take a photo?

13:09.998 --> 13:11.374
Sure thing.

13:18.006 --> 13:20.258
[camera motor buzzes]

13:22.802 --> 13:24.262
Thanks for such
a great morning, you two,

13:24.346 --> 13:26.014
but I really should head home.

13:26.097 --> 13:28.433
I have to make some of
my dad's favorite cheesy bread.

13:28.517 --> 13:31.102
- Oh.
- Is that for your ofrenda?

13:31.186 --> 13:33.021
[gasps] Yes.

13:33.104 --> 13:34.314
What's a...
Wh-What's an ofrenda?

13:34.397 --> 13:36.274
- Uh, it's...
- It's an altar made to honor

13:36.358 --> 13:38.026
those in your life
who have passed.

13:38.109 --> 13:39.319
Can I help you set it up?

13:39.402 --> 13:41.029
That's sweet, but...

13:41.112 --> 13:43.114
I did lots of reading
about the multiple levels.

13:43.198 --> 13:45.700
I could help you choose
photos of your parents.

13:45.784 --> 13:49.412
Charlie, um, I appreciate it,

13:49.496 --> 13:53.583
but my ofrenda is something
I like to do on my own. Okay?

13:53.667 --> 13:55.001
Oh, yeah. Sorry.

13:55.085 --> 13:59.381
It's fine. Um...
just have to go.

14:04.636 --> 14:06.930
Hey, it's okay.
It's all right.

14:07.013 --> 14:10.600
[phone vibrating]

14:10.684 --> 14:13.228
- Hola, Mami. ¿Qué tal?
- [Marta] Hola, mi amor.

14:13.311 --> 14:14.980
I wanted to ask if
you could take me

14:15.063 --> 14:16.648
to the storage unit today.

14:16.731 --> 14:20.026
I completely forgot my
Día de los Muertos box.

14:20.110 --> 14:22.445
Oh, don't worry about it.
I bought new decorations.

14:22.529 --> 14:24.364
The old ones were looking
a little ratty.

14:24.447 --> 14:26.700
Uh, uh, yeah,
but what about the photos?

14:26.783 --> 14:28.118
They're already up.

14:28.201 --> 14:31.079
Yes, but, well, um,
did you remember to

14:31.162 --> 14:33.290
get a picture of, um...

14:33.373 --> 14:35.041
the picture of Señor Salsa?

14:35.125 --> 14:38.211
Huh? Señor Salsa?

14:38.295 --> 14:40.755
Salcedo. Señor Salcedo.

14:40.839 --> 14:43.216
We used to call him
Señor Salsa because

14:43.300 --> 14:45.468
he used to eat a bowl of it
with a spoon.

14:45.552 --> 14:49.014
Mami, I think we can live
without a photo of Señor Salsa.

14:49.097 --> 14:52.058
Fine.
Pobrecito Señor Salcedo,

14:52.142 --> 14:53.810
you'll just have
to wait another year

14:53.893 --> 14:57.897
to pass through the veil
and enjoy a bowl of my salsa.

14:57.981 --> 14:59.899
I'm sure he'll understand.

14:59.983 --> 15:02.319
Fine. I will pick you up
in 20 minutes.

15:02.402 --> 15:04.195
Gracias.

15:06.031 --> 15:07.490
She totally bought it.

15:07.574 --> 15:09.451
Que bueno.

15:09.534 --> 15:10.869
Bought what?

15:17.334 --> 15:19.336
♪ ♪

15:24.215 --> 15:26.426
- Oh.
- Oh, shit, I am so sorry.

15:26.509 --> 15:28.678
- Oh, my God, Michael!
- Lily!

15:28.762 --> 15:29.888
Small world.

15:29.971 --> 15:31.514
Small city.

15:31.598 --> 15:33.308
I'm surprised we haven't
run into each other sooner.

15:33.391 --> 15:36.019
- How are you?
- Everything's good.

15:36.102 --> 15:37.312
Where are you off to?
[chuckles]

15:37.395 --> 15:38.980
Oh, I was just doing makeup

15:39.064 --> 15:40.023
for the Día de los Muertos gig

15:40.106 --> 15:42.025
- at the cultural center.
- Huh.

15:42.108 --> 15:46.237
- What's new with you?
- I... um...

15:46.321 --> 15:51.409
- I got married.
- Oh... wow.

15:51.493 --> 15:54.287
So in the last ten months
you found a person,

15:54.371 --> 15:57.123
dated them, got engaged,
now you're married.

15:57.207 --> 15:58.625
Cool, cool, cool.

15:58.708 --> 16:00.669
Yeah, sorry. I don't know,
maybe I should have

16:00.752 --> 16:02.045
reached out to tell you.

16:02.128 --> 16:04.839
- No, it's great.
Congratulations.
- Thank you.

16:04.923 --> 16:08.009
Thank you, that...
that means a lot.

16:08.093 --> 16:09.135
So what's new with you?

16:09.219 --> 16:10.679
Well, I am not married.

16:10.762 --> 16:12.639
[nervous laugh]

16:12.722 --> 16:15.850
In fact, I'm going through

16:15.934 --> 16:17.852
a pretty rough breakup, so...

16:17.936 --> 16:19.604
Oh, shit, I'm sorry.

16:19.688 --> 16:23.650
It's okay.
Well, I'm okay.

16:23.733 --> 16:24.984
I feel like I learned a lot.

16:26.194 --> 16:27.737
Which is what matters.

16:28.780 --> 16:30.365
Hmm.

16:30.448 --> 16:32.200
That's a new color on you.

16:32.283 --> 16:34.786
Oh, the neon pink? I thought
it was a little iffy, too.

16:34.869 --> 16:36.121
No, no, not the makeup. You.

16:36.204 --> 16:38.581
You telling me what's
really going on

16:38.665 --> 16:40.125
instead of sugarcoating it.

16:41.668 --> 16:44.254
You seem centered.

16:45.213 --> 16:46.965
It's a good look on you.

16:47.048 --> 16:49.008
Thank you.

16:51.761 --> 16:54.472
Uh, sorry, I got to,
I got to jet,

16:54.556 --> 16:59.144
but it was lovely
running into you, literally.

16:59.227 --> 17:01.146
- [both chuckle]
- Same.

17:01.229 --> 17:03.773
- Take care.
- Yeah, you, too.

17:06.109 --> 17:07.110
- Bye.
- Bye.

17:30.967 --> 17:32.135
Hola, Mami.

17:37.932 --> 17:40.685
Sorry I couldn't make it
out here last week.

17:40.769 --> 17:44.355
There was a lot going on.

17:44.439 --> 17:46.483
You want a moment
alone with her, mijo?

17:46.566 --> 17:48.610
Um, no, you can stay.

17:48.693 --> 17:51.905
Um, I don't...
Is there rules or...

17:51.988 --> 17:54.115
No, no, just if you wanted
your privacy,

17:54.199 --> 17:55.325
I wanted to be respectful.

17:55.408 --> 17:58.286
Oh, um, you didn't care
about my privacy

17:58.369 --> 17:59.496
when she was here, so...

17:59.579 --> 18:01.623
why start now?
You know what I mean?

18:01.706 --> 18:03.541
[both laugh]

18:03.625 --> 18:05.710
She'd love this.

18:05.794 --> 18:07.045
The little back and forth we do.

18:07.128 --> 18:09.506
[both chuckle]

18:09.589 --> 18:11.132
Yeah.

18:11.216 --> 18:13.051
[sighs]

18:15.970 --> 18:17.972
♪ ♪

18:28.566 --> 18:30.735
[kids laughing]

18:37.242 --> 18:40.203
[phone line trilling]

18:40.286 --> 18:43.832
Twinsies! I was
just about to call you.

18:43.915 --> 18:45.625
You'll never guess
who I ran into.

18:45.708 --> 18:47.460
Pat Sajak.

18:47.544 --> 18:49.379
In Portland?

18:49.462 --> 18:50.547
Why would that be...

18:50.630 --> 18:52.090
Lil, I don't know.
You told me to guess,

18:52.173 --> 18:53.550
so I guessed.

18:53.633 --> 18:55.134
- That's the first person
that came to my mind.
- No.

18:55.218 --> 18:57.303
Michael. I ran into Michael.

18:57.387 --> 19:00.723
No shit!
Is he still a fox?

19:00.807 --> 19:03.351
He is. And he's married.

19:03.434 --> 19:06.604
Oh. Ugh, well,

19:06.688 --> 19:08.273
I mean, I wish I was there
to day-drink with you.

19:08.356 --> 19:09.607
That sounds like a lot to hear.

19:09.691 --> 19:11.609
You know, you would've thunk.

19:11.693 --> 19:13.778
But I'm actually
really happy for him,

19:13.862 --> 19:17.323
and felt no angst or regret
or jealousy.

19:17.407 --> 19:19.450
Oh, because his wife is ugly.

19:19.534 --> 19:21.828
No. Because of growth.

19:21.911 --> 19:25.665
I'm growing, like, as a person.
Celebrate me!

19:25.748 --> 19:27.417
Lil, I mean,
that's-that's amazing.

19:27.500 --> 19:29.168
Thank you.

19:29.252 --> 19:31.546
This would have obliterated me
a year ago.

19:31.629 --> 19:33.840
But I'm totally fine.

19:35.508 --> 19:38.553
I'm... I'm really happy
for you, babe.

19:38.636 --> 19:40.513
So what's up with you?

19:43.099 --> 19:45.768
I just wanted to hear
your voice.

19:45.852 --> 19:48.354
Is everything okay?

19:48.438 --> 19:49.898
Yeah.

19:49.981 --> 19:52.859
I mean, yeah, of course.
Every-Everything is great.

19:52.942 --> 19:55.653
You know, the L.A. sun has
given my skin this, like,

19:55.737 --> 19:59.741
salted caramel kind of glow;
it's really amazing.

19:59.824 --> 20:01.868
Well, I miss you.

20:01.951 --> 20:04.871
But Thanksgiving is not
that far away. I can manage.

20:04.954 --> 20:06.247
Yeah.

20:06.331 --> 20:09.918
Yeah, yes. I can't wait
to see you then.

20:10.001 --> 20:13.212
Hmm. Hey, do you know what
happened with my rainbow serape?

20:13.296 --> 20:15.632
Sol is asking if they can borrow
it tonight for their ofrenda.

20:15.715 --> 20:18.092
I, um...

20:18.176 --> 20:19.928
- I stole it.
- Jorge,

20:20.011 --> 20:21.095
I love that blanket.

20:21.179 --> 20:22.096
Well, it's been missing
for three years,

20:22.180 --> 20:23.431
so you don't love it that much.

20:23.514 --> 20:25.058
But it's at the old apartment
if you want it.

20:25.141 --> 20:27.060
And while you're there,
you should grab Nick.

20:27.143 --> 20:28.186
Bye!

20:28.269 --> 20:30.063
[laughing] Bye.

20:47.747 --> 20:49.832
How you holding up?

20:51.376 --> 20:53.211
Not good.

20:56.756 --> 21:00.134
You know, when your mother
and I separated,

21:00.218 --> 21:02.971
that was the darkest time
in my life.

21:06.808 --> 21:09.560
I've always wanted to ask:

21:09.644 --> 21:10.979
what made you and Mom split?

21:15.858 --> 21:18.653
You know, I wish I could point
to one thing, but...

21:20.196 --> 21:24.617
I was young and dumb,
and I had to be right.

21:24.701 --> 21:27.578
- Mm.
- And your mom,

21:27.662 --> 21:31.124
she was young
and smarter than me.

21:31.207 --> 21:33.292
But I had to be right.

21:33.376 --> 21:36.129
We started spending more time
mad at each other

21:36.212 --> 21:37.755
than liking each other.

21:42.969 --> 21:44.804
That first night
away from you two,

21:44.887 --> 21:48.474
I knew I was making the biggest
mistake I ever made,

21:48.558 --> 21:52.353
but I was too stubborn
to admit I was wrong.

21:54.355 --> 21:56.816
My machismo did
a fucking number on me.

21:59.402 --> 22:01.696
It took me 16 years of bullshit
to realize

22:01.779 --> 22:03.072
that I'd rather be wrong
with her

22:03.156 --> 22:04.490
than right without her.

22:04.574 --> 22:08.119
So when did you realize
you were being a dumbass?

22:08.202 --> 22:10.079
Okay.

22:10.163 --> 22:14.625
- You. Christmas. 2015.
- Right.

22:14.709 --> 22:16.627
You insisted that
we celebrate together.

22:17.962 --> 22:18.880
I made dinner that night,

22:18.963 --> 22:23.342
and she asked me to stay.

22:23.426 --> 22:25.636
And I never left.

22:29.557 --> 22:32.518
You know, you, uh,
come from a long line

22:32.602 --> 22:34.312
of good-looking dumbasses.

22:34.395 --> 22:36.731
[chuckles]

22:36.814 --> 22:39.108
I was hoping
you'd break the cycle.

22:39.192 --> 22:41.652
Because I ain't never seen you

22:41.736 --> 22:43.488
as happy as you were
with Lily.

22:45.239 --> 22:47.825
I hope it doesn't take you
16 years to figure it out.

23:05.968 --> 23:07.887
[sharp knock on door]

23:15.895 --> 23:19.982
Uh, have you gotten more buff?

23:20.066 --> 23:22.610
Uh, actually, the proper grammar
is "buffer."

23:22.693 --> 23:24.445
And yes.

23:24.529 --> 23:26.989
[chuckles]

23:27.073 --> 23:30.409
Okay, uh, I came for my blanket.

23:30.493 --> 23:32.620
Yes, Jorge did mention.
Uh, it's on the couch.

23:32.703 --> 23:34.497
- Come on. Come in, come in.
- Okay.

23:38.793 --> 23:43.756
So, uh... I haven't seen you
in a while, Diaz.

23:43.840 --> 23:46.801
Yeah, well, uh,

23:46.884 --> 23:49.762
my phone had no service when I
was in the relationship bubble.

23:49.846 --> 23:52.223
But now that it's burst,
I've got full bars.

23:52.306 --> 23:55.476
Right, right, uh,
sorry it didn't work out

23:55.560 --> 23:56.936
between you and Santiago.

23:57.019 --> 23:58.271
Oh, it's okay.

24:00.398 --> 24:02.441
Um...

24:02.525 --> 24:04.944
I hate that this is
awkward between us.

24:05.027 --> 24:07.321
- I know, right?
Like, why, though?
- Mm-hmm.

24:07.405 --> 24:08.698
We were friends before,

24:08.781 --> 24:10.199
and we can still be
friends now.

24:10.283 --> 24:11.742
The thing is, when I see you,

24:11.826 --> 24:13.161
the first thing I think is...

24:14.036 --> 24:15.413
I've seen that guy
naked before.

24:15.496 --> 24:17.165
Oh... I've seen you naked
before.

24:17.248 --> 24:18.916
And I'm all the better for it,

24:19.000 --> 24:21.878
so, you know,
let's not make this weird.

24:21.961 --> 24:25.756
You know what, you're right.
We're both mature...

24:25.840 --> 24:27.258
- Attractive...
- ...adults

24:27.341 --> 24:29.927
who previously participated
in a mutually consensual...

24:30.011 --> 24:31.429
And very sexually
satisfying...

24:31.512 --> 24:32.972
...orgasm exchange program.

24:33.055 --> 24:34.307
Multiple in your case.

24:34.390 --> 24:36.350
Yeah. Thanks for that.

24:36.434 --> 24:39.187
My pleasure.
Well, your pleasure.

24:39.270 --> 24:41.355
- Our pleasure.
- Right.

24:41.439 --> 24:42.815
So, friends?

24:42.899 --> 24:46.068
Friends.

24:46.152 --> 24:47.987
- Oh, come on.
- Yeah.

24:49.280 --> 24:50.531
[grunts]

24:52.533 --> 24:55.203
- Split a Coke?
- Yes! Yes.

24:55.286 --> 24:58.873
Hey, uh, maybe I'll even
start wearing shirts.

24:58.956 --> 25:01.375
Hey, I never said
I wanted that to stop.

25:04.337 --> 25:05.838
[pouring soda]

25:08.382 --> 25:11.427
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

25:15.473 --> 25:17.391
[♪ Fernando Rios Roman:
"Los Metiches Sierreno"]

25:17.475 --> 25:19.477
[indistinct chatter]

25:26.776 --> 25:28.444
We ran out of al pastor.

25:28.527 --> 25:30.196
Damn, already?

25:31.489 --> 25:33.741
Thanks, Bisabuelo.

25:33.824 --> 25:36.619
♪ Andan abriendo mucho
el hocico ♪

25:36.702 --> 25:40.164
♪ Quieren saber
a qué me dedico ♪

25:40.248 --> 25:42.416
♪ Si la curiosidad mato
al gato ♪

25:42.500 --> 25:46.337
♪ Sigue tu camino
no seas insensato ♪♪

25:54.387 --> 25:56.222
[phone chimes]

25:59.725 --> 26:01.060
[laughs]

26:10.987 --> 26:14.115
- Are you sure it's here, Mami?
- Yes, I am.

26:14.198 --> 26:16.575
What are you doing here?

26:16.659 --> 26:17.910
What are you
doing here?

26:17.994 --> 26:19.412
Your dad said he needed
something.

26:19.495 --> 26:22.123
My mom said the same thing.

26:24.166 --> 26:26.127
[Marta] Work out your problems.
¡Ahora!

26:26.210 --> 26:27.628
- [Jorge Sr.] Let us out!
- [Beatriz] Yeah,

26:27.712 --> 26:29.672
or I won't help you
with the Wi-Fi again.

26:29.755 --> 26:31.549
[Luis] You two are being tontos.

26:31.632 --> 26:33.509
You have a good thing,
sort it out.

26:36.387 --> 26:38.222
They locked it.

26:40.599 --> 26:42.518
Great.

26:46.897 --> 26:48.899
♪ ♪

27:21.682 --> 27:22.683
Well...

27:24.685 --> 27:27.396
...here we are again.

27:27.480 --> 27:30.524
Still missing you.

27:30.608 --> 27:33.527
Still wishing we didn't leave
things the way we did.

27:33.611 --> 27:36.155
This year in particular
has been pretty great.

27:36.238 --> 27:40.326
I fell in love with a doctor.
Can you believe it?

27:40.409 --> 27:44.413
He's an amazing partner
and he has a very special kid.

27:44.497 --> 27:46.957
Two things you thought
I'd never have.

27:49.502 --> 27:53.005
But I have it now.

27:53.089 --> 27:55.299
I'm so happy.

27:57.718 --> 28:00.930
And I wish so much you could see
the person I've become

28:01.013 --> 28:03.265
and the family I'm creating.

28:07.770 --> 28:09.105
[phone chimes]

28:25.621 --> 28:28.541
[sighs heavily]

28:28.624 --> 28:30.126
We might as well talk.

28:30.209 --> 28:33.129
We have talked for months.

28:33.212 --> 28:37.425
But we haven't resolved
anything.

28:37.508 --> 28:39.051
I mean, is this who we are now?

28:39.135 --> 28:42.221
Technically married
but strangers in our own house?

28:44.682 --> 28:46.434
[grunts]

28:51.897 --> 28:53.816
I can't live like this, Jorge.

28:53.899 --> 28:56.569
- You need to forgive me,
or we...
- Or what?

28:56.652 --> 28:58.654
Huh?

28:58.737 --> 29:00.614
'Cause I've tried to regain
my footing in all of this,

29:00.698 --> 29:02.533
and I am lost.

29:02.616 --> 29:04.785
So, what, you're just never
gonna forgive me again?

29:04.869 --> 29:06.370
I don't know how.

29:11.250 --> 29:12.626
All I know is,
there's no going back.

29:12.710 --> 29:14.253
I don't want to go back.

29:14.336 --> 29:17.173
I want to build something new
with you for our future.

29:17.256 --> 29:20.301
But I need you to want
to build that with me.

29:20.384 --> 29:21.552
And if you don't want
to do that,

29:21.635 --> 29:22.553
you should tell me now.

29:22.636 --> 29:26.098
[breathing irregularly]

29:26.182 --> 29:27.266
Jorge?

29:28.392 --> 29:30.019
- Oh, my God. Jorge!
- [pained groans]

29:30.102 --> 29:31.937
Oh, God. Oh, my God!

29:32.021 --> 29:34.899
Mami, Papi, you need
to let us out!

29:34.982 --> 29:37.902
Something's wrong with Jorge.
We need help!

29:37.985 --> 29:40.070
Okay, okay, okay,
okay, okay.

29:41.113 --> 29:43.574
- [phone vibrating]
- A big, black bug bit
a big black bear,

29:43.657 --> 29:46.202
made the big, black bear
bleed blood.

29:46.285 --> 29:48.370
Hello, I'm Pepper Bice.

29:48.454 --> 29:51.540
Hola, me llamo Pepper Bice.

29:51.624 --> 29:54.960
Hello, I'm Pepper Bice.

29:55.044 --> 29:57.296
Hola, yo me llamo Pepper Bice.

29:57.379 --> 29:59.131
And this is the new
food truck...

29:59.215 --> 30:01.300
Oh, I'm so sorry.
This is just my process.

30:01.383 --> 30:03.677
- Oh.
- I'll let you know
when we're ready, Jorge.

30:03.761 --> 30:06.472
Yeah, great. Cool.
Sounds good.

30:07.473 --> 30:10.184
- Hello, I'm Pepper Bice.
- Hi. Hi. Yeah.

30:10.267 --> 30:11.894
This better be good.
I'm about to be on the news

30:11.977 --> 30:15.147
and say something hilarious
yet poignant, and go viral.

30:19.610 --> 30:21.445
Yeah. Yes.

30:21.529 --> 30:24.031
I-I'll be there as soon
as I can. Bye. Bye.

30:28.452 --> 30:29.954
- [speaks indistinctly]
- [phone vibrating]

30:30.037 --> 30:31.705
Oh, sorry.
Just one second.

30:31.789 --> 30:33.624
[exhales]

30:33.707 --> 30:36.544
Is this the extremely handsome
taco king of Los Angeles?

30:36.627 --> 30:38.504
My dad just had a heart attack.

30:38.587 --> 30:40.047
Oh, my God, Jorge.

30:41.715 --> 30:44.051
- I'm so sorry. Is he okay?
- I don't know.

30:44.134 --> 30:45.678
I don't know. I'm-I'm going
to the airport now.

30:45.761 --> 30:47.763
I'm gonna get on the first
flight that I can.

30:47.846 --> 30:49.557
I'll-I'll meet you there.

30:49.640 --> 30:50.975
No, no, no, there's no time.
I'll just...

30:51.058 --> 30:52.643
I'll call you as soon as
I'm taking off, all right?

30:52.726 --> 30:56.146
Okay. I love you...

30:56.230 --> 30:59.233
- so much.
- Yeah, I love you, too.

30:59.316 --> 31:00.985
Chuey, Chuey, we got to go.

31:09.994 --> 31:12.871
- Mami.
- Mija.

31:12.955 --> 31:14.582
Any news?

31:14.665 --> 31:17.209
No. Everything is
still the same.

31:17.293 --> 31:19.128
How are you holding up?

31:19.211 --> 31:21.338
I'm a wreck.

31:21.422 --> 31:23.716
This is all my fault.

31:23.799 --> 31:25.593
Mami, breathe.

31:25.676 --> 31:27.928
This has nothing
to do with you.

31:28.012 --> 31:30.764
You don't understand.

31:30.848 --> 31:34.560
We were having a fight,
and I was yelling at him.

31:34.643 --> 31:36.687
And he just keeled over.

31:36.770 --> 31:40.899
One little argument
doesn't cause a heart attack.

31:43.444 --> 31:45.696
You don't understand.

31:45.779 --> 31:48.699
It wasn't just one
little argument.

31:50.117 --> 31:51.660
We've been fighting for months.

31:51.744 --> 31:55.664
We're both so angry
all the time.

31:55.748 --> 31:58.792
What?

31:58.876 --> 32:00.502
I don't understand;
you guys are, like,

32:00.586 --> 32:02.379
the perfect couple.

32:04.089 --> 32:06.091
Why wouldn't you talk to me?

32:06.175 --> 32:09.720
Because we-we really do
love each other.

32:09.803 --> 32:13.140
And-and we wanted you and Jorge
to feel safe and secure,

32:13.223 --> 32:16.310
and know that you could
have that love, too.

32:18.771 --> 32:23.442
But love is messy, mija,
and complicated

32:23.525 --> 32:25.944
and amorphous and...

32:26.028 --> 32:27.946
it's not enough.

32:28.030 --> 32:30.407
You cannot take your eye
off the ball.

32:32.743 --> 32:36.080
A true partnership takes

32:36.163 --> 32:40.918
sweat and commitment and drive.

32:41.001 --> 32:43.545
But...

32:43.629 --> 32:46.840
you guys make it
look so easy.

32:48.801 --> 32:51.470
And I'm-I'm sorry
that we did that.

32:51.553 --> 32:55.182
But I am far from perfect,

32:55.265 --> 32:57.768
and so is your father.

33:01.105 --> 33:03.440
But I love that man.

33:03.524 --> 33:07.945
There is no one that I would
rather walk this earth with.

33:14.952 --> 33:17.705
[sobs]

33:29.174 --> 33:31.176
[airplane passing overhead]

33:33.470 --> 33:35.431
Thanks for driving.

33:35.514 --> 33:37.349
Listen, cuz, don't worry.

33:37.433 --> 33:39.518
I've had two heart attacks
and a stroke.

33:39.601 --> 33:41.145
You just got to ride
that shit out.

33:41.228 --> 33:43.522
It takes a lot more than that
to take out a Diaz.

33:43.605 --> 33:44.815
We a hearty people.

33:46.066 --> 33:47.609
Give your papi a hug for me.

33:47.693 --> 33:49.528
I will. Thanks, Chuey.

33:54.241 --> 33:55.242
Jorge.

34:02.124 --> 34:03.667
What are you doing here?

34:03.751 --> 34:06.044
There's no way I was gonna
let you go to Portland alone.

34:06.128 --> 34:09.339
Your family is my family,
Jorge Diaz.

34:09.423 --> 34:11.341
Thanks.

34:11.425 --> 34:15.387
All right, let's go.
We've got a plane to catch.

34:27.149 --> 34:30.235
- Hi.
- Hey.

34:30.319 --> 34:33.530
- It's good to see you,
Mr. Delgado.
- Good to see you.

34:36.617 --> 34:38.368
- Thank you for coming.
- Of course, of course.

34:41.538 --> 34:44.541
Say, I, um...

34:44.625 --> 34:47.419
So, how's he doing?

